annie laurie is a 1927 silent film directed by john s. robertson , released by metro-goldwyn-mayer , and starring lillian gish and norman kerry .   this was the third film of lillian gish at mgm , and its poor boxoffice returns marked a decline in the star 's career .   on a down note gish stated that her mother became ill during the production of this film and that " ... she only showed up for work " as opposed to putting her all into the film .   john wayne makes an early film appearance as a crowd extra .